**True/False Questions:**

1. **Question:** The MV<sup>2+</sup> cations in compound **1** are situated in the interlayer space.
   **Answer:** False (They are situated in the intralayer space)
   **Difficulty:** Medium
2. **Question:** The emission band at 330 nm in the luminescence spectrum of compound **1** is assigned to the MV<sup>2+</sup>-Cu<sup>II</sup> interaction.
   **Answer:** False (It is assigned to the emission of the MV<sup>2+</sup> species)
   **Difficulty:** Easy
3. **Question:** The adsorption of both CO<sub>2</sub> and CH<sub>3</sub>OH on the anhydrous derivative of compound **1** results in a blue-shift of the MV<sup>2+</sup>-Cu<sup>II</sup> emission band.
   **Answer:**  False (CO<sub>2</sub> adsorption causes a red-shift)
   **Difficulty:** Medium
4. **Question:** Compound **1** exhibits a relatively low critical temperature (T<sub>C</sub>) for its magnetic transition. 
   **Answer:** False (It exhibits a relatively high T<sub>C</sub> of 19.0 K)
   **Difficulty:** Easy
5. **Question:** The emission spectra of compound **1** remain unchanged after exposure to CH<sub>4</sub>. 
   **Answer:** True.
   **Difficulty:** Medium
6. **Question:** The anhydrous derivative of compound **1**  shows negligible adsorption of water and methanol. 
   **Answer:** False (It shows considerable adsorption of both)
   **Difficulty:** Easy
7. **Question:** The double layers in the crystal structure of compound **1** stack directly on top of each other along the b-axis. 
   **Answer:** False (They are parallelly displaced in the [100] direction)
   **Difficulty:** Hard